## Today's outcome
Slice 5: Admin shell + login UI. End state: user can navigate to /login,
sign in with real credentials, land on a protected /dashboard with the
admin sidebar/topbar visible.

## Decisions
- Phase 0 ordering: vertical slices, not backend-first
- Slice 5 starts with frontend foundation (Next.js, Tailwind, shadcn/ui)
- Tailwind v3.4 + shadcn/ui (slate base, default style), hand-authored
  the six primitives we need (button, input, label, card, dropdown-menu,
  sonner) instead of running the shadcn CLI — same output, less ceremony.
- Phase 0 auth token lives in `localStorage`; httpOnly-cookie migration
  captured in deferred.md (blocks middleware-based route protection, so
  Slice 5 uses a client-side `<RequireAuth>` gate with a branded loading
  screen — explicitly not a blank white flash).
- Sonner toaster positioned bottom-right because top-right collides with
  the topbar's profile dropdown.
- 401-mid-render: accepted brief flash. apiFetch clears the token and
  fires a custom event; AuthProvider listens, flips to `guest`, and
  routes to /login. Documented in auth-provider.tsx — chose this over
  wrapping the shell in an error boundary because the alternative adds
  plumbing for every query and the user ends up on /login either way.
- Documented apps/web vs apps/api workspace consumption divergence as a
  comment in `apps/web/next.config.mjs` (web uses transpilePackages on
  TS source; api consumes built dist/).

