## Lessons learned
- Pattern continues: backend changes that affect HTTP behaviour (env 
  loading, ESM, CORS) need manual browser verification, not just unit 
  tests
- Claude Code's honest hand-off was the right move — agents shouldn't 
  pretend to do what they can't
- Slice 5 was lighter than Prompts 3-4; vertical slices that touch new 
  surfaces (frontend) have their own friction but it surfaces differently

